---
import MarketingShell from '../components/MarketingShell.astro';
---

<MarketingShell
  title="toki-os - inspectable AI operating system"
  description="toki-os is the operating system layer behind tokigig tools, built to be inspectable, extensible, and trustworthy."
  currentPath="/os"
>
  <section class="route-hero route-hero--stub">
    <div class="route-hero__content">
      <p class="route-kicker">Toki-OS stub page</p>
      <h1>Toki-OS has a branded placeholder route ready for later build-out.</h1>
      <p class="route-lede">
        This stub keeps the route live inside the shared marketing system now, while leaving the fuller content implementation for a later step.
      </p>
      <div class="route-actions">
        <a href="/" class="btn-primary">Company home</a>
        <a href="/scan" class="btn-secondary">See TokiScan</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="route-grid-section">
    <div class="route-grid route-grid--single">
      <article class="route-card route-card--wide">
        <p class="route-card__label">Status</p>
        <h2>/os route established</h2>
        <p>The page exists, uses the same header and footer system, and gives us a clean branded destination without introducing extra product detail yet.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingShell>
